Nguyen2017-V
============

Nguyen 2017 Imagined Speech - Vowels condition.

Dataset Overview
----------------
  Code: Nguyen2017-V
  Paradigm: imagery
  DOI: 10.1088/1741-2552/aa8235
  Subjects: 8
  Sessions per subject: 1
  Events: vowel_a=1, vowel_i=2, vowel_u=3
  Trial interval: [0, 1.5] s
  File format: MAT
  Data preprocessed: True

Acquisition
-----------
  Sampling rate: 256.0 Hz
  Number of channels: 64
  Channel types: eeg=60, eog=4
  Montage: standard_1020
  Hardware: BrainProducts ActiCHamp
  Sensor type: EEG
  Line frequency: 60.0 Hz
  Online filters: {'highpass': 8.0, 'lowpass': 70.0, 'notch_hz': 60.0}

Participants
------------
  Number of subjects: 8
  Health status: healthy
  Age: min=22, max=32
  Species: human

Experimental Protocol
---------------------
  Paradigm: imagery
  Number of classes: 3
  Class labels: vowel_a, vowel_i, vowel_u
  Trial duration: 2.0 s
  Study design: Auditory beep + visual cue. 5 beeps at T=1.0s rhythm. Subject imagines speech at each beep and continues for 3 more periods. Analyzed segment: after last beep. Each 5s trial is split into 3 overlapping epochs of 2s.
  Stimulus type: auditory + visual cue
  Stimulus modalities: auditory, visual
  Primary modality: auditory
  Synchronicity: synchronous
  Mode: offline

